### 3.7 System Workflow Description

The primary workflow of StudyVault follows a linear-with-branching review process.

**Step 1 - Registration / Login:** A new user navigates to `/roles`, selects their role (Student/Faculty/Admin), and registers or logs in. The system validates credentials using `bcrypt.verify()` with constant-time comparison against a dummy hash even if the user does not exist, preventing timing attacks. Session data including user ID, name, role, and email is stored server-side by the Starlette SessionMiddleware.

**Step 2 - Note Upload (Student):** A student navigates to `/student/upload` and selects one or multiple files. On form submission, each file's extension is checked against the admin-configured allowed file types from `system_settings_collection`. Valid files are saved to `uploads/` with a unique filename. Text is extracted from the file using the appropriate library. The extracted text is sent to the Groq API via `groq_safety_analysis()`, which returns scores for six categories. The note is stored in MongoDB with `status: "pending"` and the full AI report embedded in the document.

**Step 3 - Faculty Review:** A faculty member at `/faculty/approvals` sees all pending notes in the subjects they are assigned to. They can preview the file in-browser. For each note they can Approve (note becomes visible in Browse), Reject (with a mandatory textual reason, student is notified), or Return (student receives correction request and can re-upload).

**Step 4 - Note Publication:** Approved notes appear in `/student/browse`, searchable and filterable by subject. Students can download any approved note or save it to their Favorites.

**Step 5 - Admin Oversight:** The admin dashboard provides real-time platform metrics (total users, notes by status, chart of uploads per day, faculty analytics). Admins can override any note's status, deactivate or soft-delete users, manage all announcements, and configure platform settings.

