# CHAPTER 5: RESULTS

## 5.1 Description of System Features and Results

The following major features were developed and verified as fully operational in the final system.

**Role Selection and Login:** Users are presented with a role selection screen. Selecting a role redirects to a role-specific login form. The system blocks cross-role logins and provides a generic error message to prevent credential enumeration. Session is maintained server-side using the Starlette SessionMiddleware.

**Student Dashboard:** The student dashboard displays real-time statistics: total uploads, approved notes count, pending notes, and saved favorites. The latest announcement from faculty is shown as a banner. A recent activity panel lists the five most recent notifications.

**Multi-File Note Upload with AI Analysis:** Students upload files using a drag-and-drop interface. Each uploaded file triggers the AI safety pipeline synchronously before the upload is acknowledged. The MongoDB record for the note contains a full AI report with scores in six categories and an overall Safe/Flagged verdict. This report is visible in the Faculty Approvals panel under the AI Safety modal.

**Faculty Approval Dashboard:** Faculty see a tabbed view of Pending, Approved, and Rejected notes, scoped to their subjects. Approve and Reject actions are available inline with AJAX-powered updates. The dashboard also shows performance statistics including average review time, fastest review, and slowest review across all notes reviewed.

**Browse and Download Notes:** All approved notes appear in the Browse Notes page. Students can filter by subject and search by title. Each note card shows the uploader's name and a heart icon for saving to favorites. A Download button streams the original file to the browser using FastAPI's `FileResponse`.

**AI Study Tools:** Students paste study text and choose a tool: Summary (concise bullet points), Flashcards (interactive question-answer cards), Q&A (direct question answering), or Study Guide (structured topic overview). Responses are rendered dynamically on the page using JavaScript. If the API key is unavailable, a demo mode response is delivered without crashing.

**Admin Analytics Dashboard:** The admin dashboard shows total users, total notes by status, a 7-day upload activity chart, a 7-day reports chart, and a faculty analytics table with per-faculty review counts, average review times, pending queue sizes, and current active status.

**Notifications and Messaging:** Every key platform event generates a notification for the relevant user. The bell icon in the navigation shows the live unread count updated on every page load. Private messaging supports student-to-faculty, faculty-to-student, and admin broadcast conversations. All messages are stored in the `messages` collection and displayed in grouped conversation threads.

