**Quality of available notes:** Because only faculty-approved notes appear in Browse, the platform consistently provides verified, subject-appropriate content — unlike Google Drive or Scribd where anything can be shared without any accountability.

**Reduced faculty effort:** The AI pre-screening flags obviously problematic content before faculty even open the file, reducing wasted review time on spam, plagiarised, or inappropriate material.

**Student engagement:** The AI study tools (flashcards, Q&A, guides) provide additional academic value beyond plain note sharing, giving students consistent reason to return to the platform.

**Administrative visibility:** The admin dashboard gives complete real-time visibility into platform health — user counts, note statuses, faculty response rates, and content reports — that does not exist in any of the existing systems reviewed in Chapter 2.

